Try to repair files with failed fixity

comments.body:
Testing strategy:

1. An object where we've corrupted the local isilon file
    a.  Run cloud fixity check on the FileSet with `CloudFixity::FixityRequestor.queue_resource_check!(id: {fileset_id})`. Result: success
    b. Run local fixity check on the FileSet with `LocalFixityJob.perform_now({fileset_id})`. We saw it enqueue and perform the RepairLocalFixityJob. Downloaded the file before and after. Result: successful repair.
3. An object where we've replaced the cloud file with a different tiff
    a.  Run local fixity check. Result: success
    b. Run cloud fixity check. Result: success
5. An object where we've both corrupted the local isilon file and replaced the cloud file with a different tiff
    a. run cloud fixity check (which kicks off a local fixity check as well). Result: both fail, as expected; i.e. success.

figgy.title: When Fixity Fails, Figgy should try to fix it

comments.body: What if we add an index of events that's sorted in order of updated_at? Then postgres would just have to scan down the index until it found 10 of the desired type and status.

There is currently an index on updated_at. We ran an explain on the existing query like

```
EXPLAIN SELECT * FROM orm_resources WHERE metadata @> '{ "status": ["SUCCESS"], "type": ["local_fixity"] }' AND metadata @> '{"current": [true]}' AND internal_resource = 'Event' ORDER BY updated_at DESC LIMIT 10;
```

and it's using the [path gin index](https://github.com/pulibrary/figgy/blob/main/db/migrate/20171025174720_create_path_gin_index.valkyrie_engine.rb):
```
Limit  (cost=371.63..371.66 rows=10 width=1055)
   ->  Sort  (cost=371.63..371.66 rows=10 width=1055)
         Sort Key: updated_at DESC
         ->  Bitmap Heap Scan on orm_resources  (cost=340.18..371.46 rows=10 width=1055)
               Recheck Cond: ((metadata @> '{"type": ["local_fixity"], "status": ["SUCCESS"]}'::jsonb) AND (metadata @> '{"current": [true]}'::jsonb))
               Filter: ((internal_resource)::text = 'Event'::text)
               ->  Bitmap Index Scan on index_orm_resources_on_metadata_jsonb_path_ops  (cost=0.00..340.18 rows=28 width=0)
                     Index Cond: ((metadata @> '{"type": ["local_fixity"], "status": ["SUCCESS"]}'::jsonb) AND (metadata @> '{"current": [true]}'::jsonb))
(8 rows)
```
It shows suggestions as you type and it's very hard to backspace when they're popping up.
